# Feature Architecture

LexMastery follows Feature-First Clean Architecture.

Every feature is an independent module.

Never organize by layer globally.

Incorrect

lib/

screens/

controllers/

repositories/

models/

Correct

lib/

features/

authentication/

dashboard/

courses/

quiz/

flashcards/

profile/

settings/

---

# Feature Structure

Every feature owns:

presentation/

application/

domain/

infrastructure/

routes/

tests/

No feature may directly access another feature's implementation.

---

# Layer Responsibilities

Presentation

UI

Widgets

Pages

Theme

Navigation

Application

Controllers

Providers

Use Cases

Business Orchestration

Domain

Entities

Value Objects

Repository Contracts

Business Rules

Infrastructure

API

Hive

Secure Storage

Repositories

DTOs

Mappers

---

# Dependency Rule

Presentation

↓

Application

↓

Domain

↑

Infrastructure

Domain must never depend on Flutter.

---

# Communication

Features communicate through interfaces.

Never import another feature's controller.

---

# Shared Code

Shared contains only reusable assets.

Examples

Buttons

Cards

Typography

Dialogs

Validators

Extensions

Utilities

Theme

Icons

Never place feature-specific logic in shared.

---

# Feature Independence

A feature should be removable without breaking unrelated features.

---

# Testing

Each feature owns:

Unit Tests

Widget Tests

Mocks

Fixtures

---

# Cursor Instructions

Every new feature must follow this architecture.

Never generate flat folder structures.